STATUS:chk_timezone:WARNING:8:1035:Different TIMEZONE values found
DETAILS:
byn031-15:TIMEZONE="Asia/Beijing"
byn017-7:TIMEZONE="PRC"
Recommended Action: This test is looking at TIMEZONE value in the
/etc/sysconfig/clock file, and comparing that value in all the
Nodes in the system.  We expect them to match.  You can manually
confirm the issue with the following psh/grep command:
# psh grep TIMEZONE /etc/sysconfig/clock
We find the procedure to correct this in IDA000BB252, but we will
summarize the procedure here.
1. Select one of the Nodes that shows the correct/expected value,
and logon to it.
else, if none of the Nodes have the correct/expected value just
update the following two fields:
TIMEZONE="GMT"
DEFAULT_TIMEZONE="GMT"
Note: See /usr/share/zoneinfo for a list of possible values.
2. Use pcl to distribute that file to the other Nodes in the system:
# pcl -send /etc/sysconfig/clock /etc/sysconfig
3. Shutdown the Teradata DBMS:
# tpareset -x shutting down to set TIMEZONE
4. After verifying that all the Nodes are down at Hard/Stopped
reboot the Nodes.
5. After the OS has recovered from the reboot, check the TIMEZONE
setting again as shown in the psh command above (and bring the DBMS
back up again).
